metadata.protocolName: Pilot Encapsulin Golden Gate Assembly & Transformation
metadata.author: Naail Kashif-Khan
metadata.description: Protocol to set up Golden Gate DNA assembly reactions, transform into E. coli, and plate onto a rectangular agar plate

0.name: Golden Gate Master Mix
0.description: Master Mix containing BsaI, T4 Ligase, Ligase Buffer, pSB1C3-FB vector, and ddH20

1.name: Competent Cells
1.description: Pre-made E. coli DH5alpha competent cell stock in glycerol and CaCl2

2.name: Insert gBlocks
2.description: Synthetic DNA fragments encoding pilot encapsulin designs, resuspended at 50 ng/ul in ddH20

3.name: Agar
3.description: LB Agar supplemented with 25 ug/ml chloramphenicol, 1mM IPTG, and 200 ug/ml X-gal

4.name: SOC Medium
4.description: 2% tryptone, 0.5% yeast extract, 10 mM NaCl, 2.5 mM KCl, 10 mM MgCl2, 10 mM MgSO4, and 20 mM glucose
